{"lemma":"خَبّ","slug":"خَبّ","root":"خ.ب.ب","root_slug":"خ-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9820","n9827","n9828","n9829"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to subside, to sink in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to alight and abode in a depressed tract or ground, in order that one’s place might not be known (like e. g. to avoid claims upon one’s hospitability)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become deceitful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trot, to gallop easily"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to waw, to undulate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deception, fraud, verbal noun of خَبَّ (ḵabba) (form I)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deceiver, cheater","examples":[{"text":"لَا يَدْخُلُ الْجَنَّةَ خِبٌّ وَلَا مَنَّانٌ وَلَا بَخِيلٌ","english":"The cheater, the laudicenus and the miser don’t enter paradise."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"waw, wave"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9820","headword_ar":"خَبَّ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (A, L, K,) sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabibota","text_ar":"خَبِبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealimota","text_ar":"عَلِمْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxab~u","text_ar":"يَخَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~N","text_ar":"خِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K; *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a","text_ar":"خَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [sec. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababota","text_ar":"خَبَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxub~u","text_ar":"يَخُبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqotulu","text_ar":"يَقْتُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb; [in which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~N","text_ar":"خِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is regarded as a simple subst.; but I doubt the correctness of this, and of the verb's being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatala","text_ar":"قَتَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":";])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, deceitful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked, dishonest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissimulating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mischief-maker:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, a great deceiver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very deceitful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked and deceitful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mischief-maker."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * L, TA.) [In the K and TA, neither the aor. nor the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a","text_ar":"خَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying “ he was, or became, a great deceiver, or very deceitful, ” is specified; nor the sec. pers. of the pret., which indicates the form of the aor.] ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a","text_ar":"خَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted and abode in a depressed tract of ground, in order that his place might be unknown, from a motive of niggardliness"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to avoid claims upon his hospitality, thus deceiving passers by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He denied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refused, what he possessed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a","text_ar":"خَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuxub~u","text_ar":"يُخُبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, (S, A,) deviating from a general rule, accord. to which an intrans. v. of this class [of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] should be with kesr, (MF,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababN","text_ar":"خَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiybN","text_ar":"خَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went the pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner, denoted by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababN","text_ar":"خَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as explained below;"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a horse; (S, A, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Axtb~","text_ar":"اختبّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Th, K:) and in like manner said of a man. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA taxub~u bihimu","text_ar":"جَاوُوا تَخُبُّ بِهِمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~awaAb~u","text_ar":"الدَّوَابُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came, the beasts going with them the pace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababN","text_ar":"خَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a fiY AlA^amori","text_ar":"خَبَّ فِى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababN","text_ar":"خَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hastened to begin the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a","text_ar":"خَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxub~u","text_ar":"يَخُبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA, [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) said of the sea, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, agitated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of commotion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, A, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the waves dashing together, and the winds whirling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, TA;) such being the case at a certain period, when the ships make for the shore, for safety, or cast anchor. (T, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbahumu Alxab~u","text_ar":"اَصَابَهُمُ الخَبُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Agitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commotion, of the sea, with a whirling of the winds, befell them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASAbhm xab~N","text_ar":"اصابهم خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~a bihimu AlbaHoru","text_ar":"خَبَّ بِهِمُ البَحْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sea became agitated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of commotion, with them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also, said of the dust, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It rose high:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it ran along."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And said of a plant, or of herbage, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["A","L","K","Msb","TA","S","MF","Th","T","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n9827","headword_ar":"خَبٌّ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, A, L, Msb, K) [said in the Msb to be originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~N","text_ar":"خِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) [originally an inf. n. accord. to most authorities] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~N","text_ar":"خُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) applied to a man, (S, A, L, Msb,) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~apN","text_ar":"خَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which casts doubt upon the assertion that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally an inf. n., for were it so the masc. and fem. accord. to a general rule would be the same, as well as the sing. and pl.,] applied to a woman, (JK, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great deceiver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very deceitful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * S, A, L, Msb, * K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked and deceitful; a mischief-maker;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * L, K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, guileful, artful, crafty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cunning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mak~aArN","text_ar":"مَكَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 537, in explanation of the first and second.)       -A2-  Also the first of these words,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long, elevated tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habol","text_ar":"حَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", in some copies of the K erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbl","text_ar":"جبل"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand, cleaving to the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":692},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, between two rugged tracts, in which"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. in the former of which)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are truffles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","A","L","Msb","K","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n9828","headword_ar":"خُبٌّ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobaAbN","text_ar":"اَخْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~apN","text_ar":"خِبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobaAbu AlfaHivi","text_ar":"اَخْبَابُ الفَحِثِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAyaA","text_ar":"حَوَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding guts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intestines into which the food passes from the stomach"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) thus used in the pl. form, as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~N","text_ar":"خُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bark"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liHaA='","text_ar":"لِحَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Low,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"depressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"land: (JK, K:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobaAbN","text_ar":"اَخْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuwbN","text_ar":"خُبُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n9829","headword_ar":"خِبٌّ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deceit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wickedness; dishonesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissimulation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischiefmaking;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xababN","text_ar":"خَبَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guile, art, craft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cunning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 537.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state of agitation and commotion, of the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaAbN","text_ar":"خِبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]}}